<body>
    <div class="container">
        <h1>Moroccan Salted Lemons</h1>

        <div class="ingredients">
            <h2>Ingredients</h2>
            <ul>
                <li>4 organic lemons</li>
                <li>4 tablespoons coarse sea salt</li>
                <li>Juice of 2 lemons</li>
                <li>Optional spices: bay leaves, cinnamon sticks, or cloves</li>
                <li>Boiled and sterilized glass jar</li>
            </ul>
        </div>

        <div class="instructions">
            <h2>Instructions</h2>
            <ol>
                <li>Wash the lemons thoroughly and cut them lengthwise into quarters, but do not cut all the way through. Keep the lemons intact at the base.</li>
                <li>Sprinkle 1 tablespoon of coarse sea salt inside each lemon and press them gently back into shape.</li>
                <li>Place the salted lemons in the sterilized glass jar, layering them tightly. Add additional spices like bay leaves, cinnamon, or cloves between the lemons, if desired.</li>
                <li>Pour the juice of 2 lemons into the jar and fill the remaining space with boiled, cooled water until the lemons are fully submerged.</li>
                <li>Seal the jar tightly and store it in a cool, dark place for 4 weeks, shaking the jar gently every few days to distribute the salt.</li>
                <li>Once the lemons are ready, store them in the refrigerator and use as needed in Moroccan dishes or as a flavorful condiment.</li>
            </ol>
        </div>

        <div class="footer">
            <p>Recipe adapted from GaultMillau. Enjoy your Moroccan culinary journey!</p>
        </div>
    </div>
